reviewText: better than you think it is, low budget fun

It's clearly a home- made flavor movie, but it actually was a pretty good tell. The worms are some pretty bad boys, as well. With a little more production money, I'm guessing the sequel will be better. Pretty scary.

"Four years have swiftly gone by since this film quietly made debut in 2012 and has finally landed onto DVD from the fine folks at Camp Motion Pictures! Rotgut has undeservingly gone under the radar, but it shall no more, gifting audiences with supreme worm mayhem and bloodshed. "
